.TH "efi_load_initrd_dev_path" 9 "efi_load_initrd_dev_path" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
efi_load_initrd_dev_path \- load the initrd from the Linux initrd device path
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "efi_status_t" efi_load_initrd_dev_path
.BI "(unsigned long *load_addr "  ","
.BI "unsigned long *load_size "  ","
.BI "unsigned long max "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "load_addr" 12
pointer to store the address where the initrd was loaded
.IP "load_size" 12
pointer to store the size of the loaded initrd
.IP "max" 12
upper limit for the initrd memory allocation
.SH "RETURN"
* EFI_SUCCESS if the initrd was loaded successfully, in which
case \fIload_addr\fP and \fIload_size\fP are assigned accordingly
* EFI_NOT_FOUND if no LoadFile2 protocol exists on the initrd device path
* EFI_INVALID_PARAMETER if load_addr == NULL or load_size == NULL
* EFI_OUT_OF_RESOURCES if memory allocation failed
* EFI_LOAD_ERROR in all other cases
